Package: p2ptunnel
Version: __VERSION__
Section: net
Priority: optional
Architecture: __ARCH__
Maintainer: webrtc_tunnel maintainers <noreply@example.invalid>
Depends: libc6 (>= 2.34), adduser
Recommends: systemd
Homepage: https://github.com/ekkus93/webrtc_tunnel
Description: WebRTC-based peer-to-peer TCP tunnel (offer/answer daemons)
 p2p-offer and p2p-answer are foreground daemons that tunnel TCP traffic
 between two peers over an encrypted WebRTC data channel, using MQTT for
 out-of-band signaling only. Includes p2pctl for identity/config management.
 .
 Installs the binaries and systemd unit files; does not create a default
 configuration. See /usr/share/doc/p2ptunnel/ (README, SYSTEMD.md) after
 install for setup steps.
